    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Dissolve the <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> in 500ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[1L]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-loin-with-tomato-orzo-and-basil-vinaigrette/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a medium sized pot with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[3 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, and the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-loin-with-tomato-orzo-and-basil-vinaigrette/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>orzo</strong> to the pot with the <strong>chicken stock</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium-low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until cooked through</p><p>Tip: Stir the orzo occasionally to stop it from sticking!</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-loin-with-tomato-orzo-and-basil-vinaigrette/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop the <strong>basil</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Combine the <strong>chopped basil </strong>and <strong>white wine vinegar</strong> with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>basil vinaigrette</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-loin-with-tomato-orzo-and-basil-vinaigrette/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Pat the <strong>pork loin steaks</strong> dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>steaks</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 4-5 min on each side or until they're browned and cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Once done, transfer the cooked steaks to a clean chopping board, cover with a clean tea towel and leave them to rest for 2 min</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-loin-with-tomato-orzo-and-basil-vinaigrette/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the orzo is cooked, add the <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong> to the pot with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, <strong>pepper</strong> and <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Cook for 2-3 min further or until the sauce has thickened slightly \u2013 this is your <strong>tomato orzo</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-loin-with-tomato-orzo-and-basil-vinaigrette/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash the <strong>rocket</strong> and pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Slice the <strong>rested pork steaks</strong> into strips</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-loin-with-tomato-orzo-and-basil-vinaigrette/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>tomato orzo</strong> in bowls and top with the <strong>sliced pork steaks</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>rocket</strong> to the side and drizzle the <strong>basil vinaigrette </strong>all<strong> </strong>over</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
